{"_path":"/posts/nvidia-cuda-55ubuntu-1310-saucy-salamander","_dir":"posts","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Nvidia CUDA 5.5/Ubuntu 13.10 Saucy Salamander","description":"A guide on how to get CUDA 5.5 installed in Ubuntu 13.10 Saucy Salamander.","imagesource":null,"imagecredit":null,"imageFilename":"2014.01.23T070000_nvidia-cuda-55ubuntu-1310-saucy-salamander.png","createdAt":"2014-01-23T07:00:00","updatedAt":"2014-01-23T07:00:00","readingTime":{"text":"1 min read","minutes":0.34,"time":20400,"words":68},"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hey guys. Had a small amount of trouble recently installing cuda 5.5 on "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://www.ubuntu.com","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ubuntu 13.10 Saucy Salamander"}]},{"type":"text","value":" recently, and none of the guides I saw seemed to give the complete story, as "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"cuda 5.5"}]},{"type":"text","value":" isn't compatible with Saucy's default gcc version. This is actually more of a guide on how to use update-alternatives than anything specific for cuda itself. Anyway, onwards..."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It's actually a pretty simple process. Following instructions found "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://www.r-tutor.com/gpu-computing/cuda-installation/cuda5.5-ubuntu","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://gerfficient.com/2013/11/11/getting-opencl-1-1-running-in-ubuntu-13-10/","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here"}]},{"type":"text","value":", I was able to see that the process should be fairly simple, but it still wouldn't install. The issue was it didn't support gcc-4.8. Reading into it, I needed to be using gcc 4.7.2 or before, so neither Saucy's 4.8 (4.8.1) or 4.7 (4.7.3) options would work. I needed gcc-4.6 to be picked up by the OS as the default compiler. Cue update-alternatives."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First up you need to install the gcc-4.6 binaries. This is as simple as:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark","code":"apt-get install gcc-4.6 g++-4.6\n","language":"bash","meta":"","style":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":1},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#B392F0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"apt-get"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" install"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" gcc-4.6"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" g++-4.6\n"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now you need to set up gcc (and g++ if you like) with their alternatives, and defaults."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark","code":"sudo update-alternatives --remove-all gcc\nsudo update-alternatives --remove-all g++\nsudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-4.6 30\nsudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/g++ g++ /usr/bin/g++-4.6 30\nsudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-4.7 20\nsudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/g++ g++ /usr/bin/g++-4.7 20\nsudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-4.8 10\nsudo update-a